<br>
Given a warrior and rogue of the same level (pre50, maybe pre 40, since he was making an example of level 3<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> , and given that they both have equipment they could have reasonably obtained for their level (without doing the trade game to get what's usually considered twink gear, too), that the rogue won't outdamage the warrior due to the apparent fact that rogue usable weapons have inferior ratios to warrior useable weapons at these levels.<br>
<br>
Now, in my experience, this wasn't the case.  When I was 38 (just before I upgraded to a Crys Spear) I was using a Crystal Grinder (9/27) and Burning Rapier (7/20).  And I regularly had to evade with warriors playing tank at my level.  And I earned those two weapons my self (Rapier around 26, Grinder ... 35 or so, IIRC).<br>
<br>
I can't make an arguement as to ratios, but I can say that I regularly outdamaged, or at least outtaunted (since I started keeping others hits off to avoid battlespam problems) warriors regularly at these levels.<br>
<br>
So honestly, decl, I'm not entirely sure where you're getting your information, because my experience is different (and I'm admittedly not one of those old school rogues who was around since rogues sucked, so I did my 30s a couple months after Velious came out, which apparently had something to do with your argument). <p>Tenbil En`Haldar<br>
